                </div>
                <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">What are the main modules in SAP Ariba?</h4>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">The main modules are SAP Ariba Sourcing, SAP Ariba Contracts, SAP Ariba Supplier Lifecycle & Performance (SLP), SAP Ariba Procurement, SAP Ariba Spend Analysis, and SAP Ariba Supplier Risk Management.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">What is the Ariba Network?</h4>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">The Ariba Network is the largest B2B trading network in the world that links thousands of buyers and suppliers from different parts of the world. It supports the exchange of business documents, invoicing, and trading partners'' collaboration.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">What is the difference between SAP Ariba and SAP SRM?</h4>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">SAP SRM (Supplier Relationship Management) is an on-premise solution that needs to be installed and maintained. On the other hand, SAP Ariba is a cloud solution, offering more flexibility, automatic updates, and access from anywhere there''s Internet.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">What is Guided Buying in SAP Ariba?</h4>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Guided Buying is a process undertaken in SAP Ariba Buying that helps users to manage procurement more easily. It resembles a typical online shopping interface which makes it easier for employees to search for and make orders for pre-approved items.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">What is SAP Ariba Supplier Lifecycle and Performance (SLP)?</h4>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Managing supplier relations at all stages is what SAP Ariba SLP is about, from supplier registration and qualification to performance evaluation and risk management.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">How does SAP Ariba certification benefit my career?</h4>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">SAP Ariba certification validates your expertise in procurement and supply chain management, making you more competitive in the job market. It demonstrates your knowledge of cloud-based procurement solutions and can lead to better career opportunities and higher salaries.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">What are downstream processes in SAP Ariba?</h4>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Downstream processes in SAP Ariba are activities that take place after sourcing. These include procurement execution, invoicing, payments, and working with suppliers on fulfillment.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

